<div class="comment comment-even" id="comment-6a00d8341ef22f53ef0120a8c9f3f3970b">
	<div class="comment-content" id="comment-6a00d8341ef22f53ef0120a8c9f3f3970b-content">
		<span id="comment-6a00d8341ef22f53ef0120a8c9f3f3970b-content"><p>Mireille, who asked about how to store bread for later use. I buy 2-3 baguettes at a time to save on trips to the bakery, and cut and put them in zip lock bags and store them in the refrigerator. They keep for over week this way. Before making a sandwich, toast the bread in a toaster oven for a couple of minutes, which makes the outside crunchy. </p></span>
	</div>
	<p class="comment-footer">
